A NOTE ON CAPACITORS
If you are trying to add the capacitors to multiply your analogue input as explained in the previous
FAQ (AF1upgrI.lha), mind the fact that you must use AnaCal in the same screenmode of VGP to get
the right values. VGP tries to open a CGFX screen (if you have got a gfx-board) otherwise it goes
for MULTISCAN, DBLPAL or PAL in this order depending on the availability of the "Monitors" files
in your DEVS:Monitors/ drawer.
So, if you play VGP in MULTISCAN, you must start the analogue test utility from anacal.lha in
MULTISCAN too, otherwise you'll get erroneus readings and you won't be able to find out the right
capacitors values (the Amiga's analogue input circuitry is screenmode-dependant)

